CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 30, 1959, pg. 2, reads: "Branch Rickey Sr...pleads for housing equality." Portion of accompanying article reads: "'Give Negroes a Chance At Good Homes' - Rickey - HARRISBURG - Lending credence to the contention that he is a bonafide champion of human rights, Branch Rickey Sr., who opened baseball's door to Negro players, made an impassioned plea for equal housing opportunities and other minority groups..."
TitMainTitle: Baseball executive Branch Rickey Sr. speaking about equal housing rights, in Wesley Center AME Zion Church, with another man on right
